quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  36,76,"So let not their speech grieve you. Indeed, We know what they conceal and what they declare."
  36,77,"Does man not consider that We created him from a [mere] sperm-drop - then at once{1} he is a clear adversary?",footnotes:1:i.e., as soon as he becomes self-sufficient.
  36,78,"And he presents for Us an example{1} and forgets his [own] creation. He says, ",footnotes:1:Attempting to establish the finality of death.
  37,61,"For the like of this let the workers [on earth] work."
  37,62,"Is that [i.e., Paradise] a better accommodation or the tree of zaqqūm?"
  37,63,"Indeed, We have made it a torment for the wrongdoers."
  38,40,"And indeed, for him is nearness to Us and a good place of return."
  38,41,"And remember Our servant Job, when he called to his Lord, "
  38,42,"[So he was told], "
  39,25,"Those before them denied, and punishment came upon them from where they did not perceive."
  39,26,"So Allāh made them taste disgrace in worldly life. But the punishment of the Hereafter is greater, if they only knew."
  39,27,"And We have certainly presented for the people in this Qur’ān from every [kind of] example - that they might remember."
  40,4,"No one disputes concerning the signs of Allāh except those who disbelieve, so be not deceived by their [uninhibited] movement throughout the land."
  40,5,"The people of Noah denied before them and the [disbelieving] factions after them, and every nation intended [a plot] for their messenger to seize him, and they disputed by [using] falsehood to [attempt to] invalidate thereby the truth. So I seized them, and how [terrible] was My penalty."
  40,6,"And thus has the word [i.e., decree] of your Lord come into effect upon those who disbelieved that they are companions of the Fire."